The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Timeout

 Not a small loss

 Synthesizing elements from different Indian classical and folk dances in Uday Shankars unique style of Indian creative dance, the compositions of Shanti Bose are adaptable to various kinds of music, themes and moods. This evenings presentation mainly features choreographed renditions of Tagores verse creations. It begins with Bhumipranam, which invokes the blessings of Mother Earth. The central offering of the programme is Samanya Kshati, a ballet. Based on Tagores poem, (a scene from the ballet appears above) is about a king who decides to punish his queen in order to maintain justice in his kingdom and be true to his conscience. An innovative presentation, it combines several dance forms of India, including folk and classical. Also to be performed is Kartikeya, a solo performance in pure Kathakali style by Bose, Ganga, a folk dance of Bengal, Land of Cards, an excerpt from Tagores Tasher Desh and Madira, a folk dance from Madhya Pradesh. Direction: Shanti Bose and Sunanda Bose.

